article.headline: Long Beach State 55, UC Irvine 50
article.story: LONG BEACH, Calif. (AP) -- Jibril Hodges scored 15 points to lead Long Beach State to a 55-50 victory over UC Irvine Thursday. Hodges made six of 10 shots as the 49ers (6-18, 4-10 Big West Conference) won their third consecutive game for the first time since February 2002. The Anteaters (11-11, 5-9) have lost four of five and dropped to 5-7 on the road. Adam Metelski's basket with 1:54 remaining cut the Long Beach lead to 53-50 but UC Irvine did not score the rest of the way. Irvine coach Pat Douglass was called for a technical foul with 19 seconds left for protesting that UC Irvine guard Davis Baker was fouled on a 3-point attempt. Hodges converted one of two free throws and Kevin Houston added a free throw with 10 seconds remaining as the 49ers held on to win. Shawn Hawkins scored 12 points and had eight rebounds for the 49ers. Houston added 11 points for Long Beach State, which beat UC Irvine for just the third time in 11 games. Greg Ethington led UC Irvine with 17 points and eight rebounds. The Anteaters went 1-for-11 from behind the 3-point line, and shot just 32 percent in the second half.
